2Fca%2F550d9b9f4472b09254f6c77653ce%2Fpodcast-1.png", "https://nbcsports.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/5d115f7/2147483647/strip/true/crop/214x214+3+0/resize/20x20!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-sports-production-nbc-sports.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbrightspot%2F71%2F4b%2Fd0ff247bc9644abeb9459412315f%2Fnbc-sports1.png", "https://nbcsports.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/2c0a227/2147483647/strip/true/crop/512x512+0+0/resize/20x20!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-sports-production-nbc-sports.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbrightspot%2Fb0%2F61%2F1d68ac744c90a47dbfe925f0a31f%2Fnbcsbaca.png", "https://nbcsports.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/370d426/2147483647/strip/true/crop/512x512+0+0/resize/20x20!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-sports-production-nbc-sports.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbrightspot%2Fff%2F2c%2Fd1e140d64f4ead3d2e6c2cc55e98%2Fnbcsbos.png", "https://nbcsports.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/f337463/2147483647/strip/true/crop/512x512+0+0/resize/20x20!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-sports-production-nbc-sports.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbrightspot%2Fb5%2Fc2%2Fff91048a4d72af57ac4200b2e5d3%2Fnbcsphi.png", "https://nbcsports.brightspotcdn.com/dims4/default/9c3454f/2147483647/strip/true/crop/4096x1039+0+504/resize/544x138!/quality/90/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fnbc-sports-production-nbc-sports.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com%2Fbrightspot%2F00%2F86%2F1cc2e11b4590b52881ac84abe4a7%2Ffavoritesmodalbackground.jpeg"], "publication-date": "2024-08-11", "text": "The 2024 Olympics in Paris are in full flow and the soccer tournaments have been absolutely enthralling.\n\nAnd now we’re into the final few games, with the bronze and gold medal matches taking place over the next few days.\n\n[ LIVE:Watch every soccer game at Paris 2024 Olympics]\n\nWith stadiums across France (Bordeaux, Lyon, Nice, Marseille, Nantes and Saint-Etienne will host games) being used and the final held at Paris Saint-Germain’s Parc des Princes home, this has been an epic celebration of the beautiful game.\n\n[ MORE:How does it work?]\n\nBelow you will find details on who has qualified for the 2024 Olympics in both the men’s and women’s soccer tournaments, while you can click on the link for details about how to watch all of the Olympic action across NBC’s platforms.\n\n\n\nDates: July 25 - August 10TV: USA Network, E!, other NBC channelsOnline:Watch on Peacock\n\n\n\nBronze medal match\n\nFriday, August 9: Spain 0-1 Germany (Lyon) -Recap & highlights\n\nGold medal match\n\nSaturday, August 10: Brazil 0-1 USA (Paris) -Recap, highlights & analysis\n\n\n\nBronze medal match\n\nThursday, August 8: Egypt 0-6 Morocco (Nantes)- Morocco wins bronze medal\n\nGold medal match\n\nFriday, August 9: France 3-5 (AET) Spain (Paris) -Highlights, recap & analysis-Spain wins gold medal, France wins silver\n\n\n\nSemifinals\n\nTuesday, August 6: USA 1-0 (AET) Germany (Lyon) -Recap, highlights, analysisTuesday, August 6: Spain 2-4 Brazil (Marseille)\n\nQuarterfinals\n\nQuarterfinal 2: Saturday, August 3: USA 1-0 (AET) Japan (Paris) -Highlights, recap & analysisQuarterfinal 3: Saturday, August 3: Spain 2-2 (4-2 PKs) Colombia (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 4: Saturday, August 3: Canada 0-0 (2-4 PKs) Germany (Marseille) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 1: Saturday, August 3: France 0-1 Brazil (Nantes) -Recap & highlights\n\nThursday, July 25\n\nCanada 2-1 New Zealand (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlightsFrance 3-2 Colombia (Lyon) -Recap & highlights\n\nSunday, July 28\n\nNew Zealand 0-2 Colombia (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsFrance 1-2 Canada (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlights\n\nWednesday, July 31\n\nNew Zealand 1-2 France (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsColombia 0-1 Canada (Nice) -Recap & highlights\n\nThursday, July 25\n\nGermany 3-0 Australia (Marseille) -Recap & highlightsUSA 3-0 Zambia (Nice) -Recap, highlights & analysis\n\nSunday, July 28\n\nAustralia 6-5 Zambia (Nice) -Recap & highlightsUSA 4-1 Germany (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysis\n\nWednesday, July 31\n\nZambia 1-4 Germany (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlightsAustralia vs USA, 1pm (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysis\n\nThursday, July 25\n\nSpain 2-1 Japan (Nantes) -Recap & highlightsNigeria 0-1 Brazil (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights\n\nSunday, July 28\n\nBrazil 1-2 Japan (Paris) -Recap & highlightsSpain 1-0 Nigeria (Nantes) -Recap & highlights\n\nWednesday, July 31\n\nJapan 3-1 Nigeria (Nantes) -Recap & highlightsBrazil 0-2 Spain (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights\n\n\n\nQuarterfinals\n\nQuarterfinal 2: Friday, August 2: Morocco 4-0 USA, 9am ET (Paris) -Highlights, recap & analysisQuarterfinal 4: Friday, August 2: Japan 0-3 Spain (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 3: Friday, August 2: Egypt 1-1 (5-4 PKs) Paraguay (Marseille) -Recap & highlightsQuarterfinal 1: Friday, August 2: France 1-0 Argentina (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights\n\nSemifinals\n\nMonday, August 5: Morocco 1-2 Spain (Marseille)Monday, August 5: France 3-1 Egypt (Lyon) AET\n\nWednesday, July 24\n\nGuinea 1-2 New Zealand (Nice) -Recap & highlightsFrance 3-0 USA (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysis\n\nSaturday, July 27\n\nNew Zealand 1-4 USA (Marseille) -Recap, highlights & analysisFrance 1-0 Guinea (Nice) -Recap & highlights\n\nTuesday, July 30\n\nNew Zealand 0-3 France (Marseille)USA 3-0 Guinea (Saint-Etienne) -Recap, highlights & analysis\n\nWednesday, July 24\n\nArgentina 1-2 Morocco (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlightsIraq 2-1 Ukraine (Lyon) -Recap & highlights\n\nSaturday, July 27\n\nArgentina 3-1 Iraq (Lyon) -Recap & highlightsUkraine 2-1 Morocco (Saint-Etienne) -Recap & highlights\n\nTuesday, July 30\n\nUkraine 0-2 Argentina (Lyon)Morocco 3-0 Iraq (Nice)\n\nWednesday, July 24\n\nUzbekistan 1-2 Spain (Paris) -Recap & highlightsEgypt 0-0 Dominican Republic (Nantes) -Recap & highlights\n\nSaturday, July 27\n\nDominican Republic 1-3 Spain (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlightsUzbekistan 0-1 Egypt (Nantes) -Recap & highlights\n\nTuesday, July 30\n\nDominican Republic 1-1 Uzbekistan - (Paris)Spain 1-2 Egypt - (Bordeaux)\n\nWednesday, July 24\n\nJapan 5-0 Paraguay (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlightsMali 1-1 Israel (Paris) -Recap & highlights\n\nSaturday, July 27\n\nIsrael 2-4 Paraguay (Paris) -Recap & highlightsJapan 1-0 Mali (Bordeaux) -Recap & highlights\n\nTuesday, July 30\n\nParaguay 1-0 Mali (Paris)Israel 0-1 Japan (Nantes)\n\n\n\nFor the first time since 2008 the USMNT have qualified for the tournament and there will be hopes that a talented young squad can deliver a medal for Team USA as they were handed a kind group stage draw where they face hosts France in the opening game. Two-time reigning champs Brazil failed to qualify so hosts France and reigning World Cup champs Argentina are the favorites to win gold. The men’s tournament is a U-23 competition but three players in each squad over the age of 23 are allowed to compete for their nations. With Achraf Hakimi, Michael Olise, Julian Alvarez and plenty of other stars competing in the men’s tournament, it’s going to be a beauty.\n\n[ MORE:United States men’s roster for 2024 Paris Olympics]\n\nThe USWNT have qualified for the women’s tournament (which allows players of all ages to compete) and are favorites to win gold in Paris under new head coach Emma Hayes, but they haven’t tasted success at the Olympics since 2012 in London as Canada are the reigning champs. The USWNT were handed a very tough group with Germany, Australia and Zambia set to push them all the way to reach the knockout rounds. Hosts France are also expected to make a deep run, while Canada, Brazil, reigning World Cup champs Spain and Japan are all expected to push for the gold medal.\n\nThere are 12 teams in the women’s tournament with the USWNT clinching their qualifying spot by winning the CONCACAF W Championship in 2022. Canada beat Jamaica in a CONCACAF playoff as the reigning champs reached the Olympics, while Brazil and Colombia will represent South America. France qualify as hosts, while Germany and Spain qualified as UEFA Nations League Finals third-place winner and finalist respectively. New Zealand represent the Oceania region, while Japan and Australia will represent Asia and Nigeria and Zambia will fly the flag for Africa after coming out of their qualifying tournament.\n\nAFC (Asia): Japan, Australia\n\nCAF (Africa): Nigeria, Zambia\n\nCONMEBOL (South America): Brazil, Colombia\n\nCONCACAF (Central & North America): Canada, USA\n\nOFC (Oceania): New Zealand\n\nUEFA: France (host), Spain, Germany\n\n\n\nGroup stage draw\n\n\n\nGroup A: France, Colombia, Canada, New Zealand\n\nGroup B: USWNT, Zambia, Germany, Australia\n\nGroup C: Spain, Japan, Nigeria,Brazil\n\nThere are 16 teams in the men’s tournament with three teams from Asia, Africa and Europe, plus two from South America and Central and North America, one from Oceania and France as hosts, qualifying for the tournament. The final team to make it was Guinea as they won the AFC-CAF playoff.\n\n\n\nAFC (Asia): Iraq, Japan, Uzbekistan\n\nCAF (Africa): Egypt, Mali, Morocco\n\nCONMEBOL (South America): Argentina, Paraguay\n\nCONCACAF (Central & North America): Dominican Republic, USA\n\nOFC (Oceania): New Zealand\n\nUEFA (Europa): France (host), Israel, Spain, Ukraine\n\nAFC-CAF playoff: Guinea\n\n\n\nGroup stage draw\n\n\n\nGroup A: France, USA, Guinea, New Zealand\n\nGroup B: Argentina, Morocco, Iraq, Ukraine\n\nGroup C: Uzbekistan, Spain, Egypt, Dominican Republic\n\nGroup D: Japan, Paraguay, Mali, Israel\n\nA Division ofNBCUniversal.\n\nDISCLAIMER: This site and the products offered are for entertainment purposes only, and there is no gambling offered on this site. This service is intended for adult audiences. No guarantees are made for any specific outcome. If you or someone you know has a gambling problem, please call 1-800-GAMBLER.\n\nⒸ 2024 NBC Universal", "title": "2024 Paris Olympics: How to watch live, updates, schedule, live scores, brackets, tables - NBC Sports", "top-image": "https://nbcsports.brightspotcdn.com/76/a1/28ae939d488781e23e1813aaecb3/nbc-sports-logo-1.svg", "domain": "www.nbcsports.com", "lang": "en-US", "author": "", "description": "The soccer tournaments at the 2024 Olympics in Paris have been incredible viewing and we're now into the medal games.", "keywords": ""}